{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Endo-FM [18] was pre-trained under a teacherstudent scheme via spatial-temporal matching on diverse video views.",
    "Both teacher and student models process these views of a video and predict one view from another in the latent feature space.",
    "LVM-Med [134] was pre-trained on 1.3 million images from 55 publicly available datasets, covering a large number of organs and modalities via a second-order graph matching.",
    "Wu et al. [135] proposed a simple yet effective VoCo framework to leverage the contextual position priors for pre-training.",
    "Besides, MIS-FM [137] introduced a pretext task based on pseudo-segmentation, where Volume Fusion (VF) was proposed to generate paired images and segmentation labels to pre-train the 3D segmentation model."
  ],
